// Design Templates and Design Tokens
// Pre-built UI component templates and design token presets that let Claude
// create common UI elements and variable collections without building raw scene graphs.

Four token presets are available: material, ios, minimal-dark, minimal-light.
Each preset defines colors, typography, spacing, and radii variables.
Templates (navbar, card, button, input, list-item, avatar, badge, modal, tab-bar, form)
return tree specs compatible with create_design_from_tree.

FUNCTION generateNavbar(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a horizontal auto-layout FRAME containing back button, title, and action text nodes.
  Customizable via: title, fill, textColor, width, height.

---

FUNCTION generateCard(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a vertical auto-layout FRAME with an image placeholder rectangle and content area
  containing title and subtitle text. Customizable via: title, subtitle, fill, width, imageHeight.

---

FUNCTION generateButton(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a centered horizontal FRAME containing a label TEXT node.
  Customizable via: label, fill, textColor, width, height, cornerRadius.

---

FUNCTION generateInput(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a vertical FRAME with an optional label TEXT and a bordered input field FRAME
  containing placeholder text. Customizable via: placeholder, label, width, height.

---

FUNCTION generateListItem(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a horizontal FRAME containing an avatar ellipse, text content area (title + optional subtitle),
  and a chevron. Customizable via: title, subtitle, width, height.

---

FUNCTION generateAvatar(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a circular FRAME containing initials TEXT. Size, fill, initials, and text color are customizable.

---

FUNCTION generateBadge(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a small circular FRAME containing a count TEXT node.
  Customizable via: text, fill, textColor, size.

---

FUNCTION generateModal(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a full-screen overlay FRAME (390x844, semi-transparent black) containing a centered
  modal card with title, body text, and Cancel/Confirm buttons.
  Customizable via: title, body, width, fill.

---

FUNCTION generateTabBar(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a horizontal FRAME containing evenly-spaced tab items (icon ellipse + label text).
  First tab gets activeColor, others get inactiveColor.
  Customizable via: items[], fill, activeColor, inactiveColor, width.

---

FUNCTION generateForm(params?) -> TreeSpec
  Build a vertical card FRAME containing a title, one input field per provided field spec,
  and a submit button. Customizable via: title, fields[{label, placeholder}], width, submitLabel.

---

FUNCTION generateId() -> string
  Returns a short unique ID combining timestamp (base36) and random characters.
  Used internally for variable and collection IDs.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateFromTemplate(project, session, designId, template, params?, parentId?) -> { nodeIds, rootNodeId }  EXPORT
  CALLS: handleCreateDesignFromTree (design-ai)
  Look up the generator function for the requested template name.
  Call the generator with provided params to produce a tree spec.
  Delegate to handleCreateDesignFromTree to add the tree into the design.

---

FUNCTION handleCreateDesignTokens(project, session, designId, preset?, custom?) -> { collectionId, variableIds }  EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Resolve the token set from the named preset or caller-provided custom tokens.
  Load the design and ensure variableCollections and variables arrays exist.
  Create a variable collection with a single Default mode.
  For each token category present:
    - Colors: create a COLOR variable per entry, converting hex to normalized RGBA.
    - Typography: create a FLOAT variable for fontSize and fontWeight per entry.
    - Spacing: create a FLOAT variable per entry.
    - Radii: create a FLOAT variable per entry.
  Append the collection record. Save design. Return collectionId and all created variable IDs.

---

FUNCTION handleApplyDesignTokens(project, session, designId, nodeId, bindings) -> { appliedBindings }  EXPORT
  CALLS: handleGetDesign (design), handleUpdateDesign (design)
  Load the design. Find the target node by nodeId.
  For each binding (property → variable name), locate the variable by name in the design's
  variables array and bind it to the node's property via boundVariables.
  Throw if any referenced variable is not found. Save design. Return map of property → variable ID.
